# 8. もどかしい想い

Honami: Ms. Yoisaki, I'm all done cleaning now.
Honami: I've also made enough food for two, so please feel free to eat it whenever you two like.
Kanade: Thank you, Ms. Mochizuki. I apologize for adding so much to your work order.
Honami: No, please don't let that bother you. I do get paid more for doing this.
Honami: Anyway, if you'll excuse me...
Honami: So, um... How is Asahina doing?
Kanade: Oh, she just fell asleep while working. It's not like she isn't feeling well today.
Honami: Oh, I see. That's good to hear...
Honami: No, I'm sorry! I didn't mean to pry or anything.
Honami: Please give her my regards.
Kanade: Thank you. I'll do that...
Kanade: (I really can't thank her enough...)
Kanade: (Ms. Mochizuki was pretty startled when she learned that Mafuyu would be staying with me for a little while...)
Honami: Asahina...
Kanade: So, she'll be staying with me for a little while.
Honami: Umm... How long is “a little while”...?
Kanade: That's hard for me to say. Days. Possibly longer...
Kanade: Actually, she may end up staying here long term...
Honami: I see...
Kanade: I'm sorry. I can't divulge much more than that...
Honami: ...
Honami: Something happened that led to her staying over at your house, yes...?
Kanade: Yes...
Honami: Okay, then I understand what I need to do.
Honami: I'll do my best to make enough food for both you and Asahina.
Kanade: Th-Thank you, Ms. Mochizuki...
Honami: There's no need to thank me.
Honami: Please feel free to let me know if you need anything, Asahina.
Mafuyu: Thank you...
Kanade: Thank goodness... She's sound asleep.
Kanade: (Quite a lot of time has passed since Mafuyu first came over...)
Kanade: (She seems okay whenever we're working together... But I've noticed her sinking from time to time.)
Kanade: (I suppose it's only natural given her situation.)
Kanade: (But isn't there anything else I can do for her...?)
Kanade: (After speaking with Mafuyu's parents, and along with Ms. Mochizuki's help, she's been able to settle in nicely here.)
Kanade: (But she can't stay here forever.)
Kanade: (Once things actually settle down... She has to talk to her dad. And her mom.)
Kanade: (That's probably going to be incredibly painful for her...)
Kanade: (Which is why I want to support her as best I can.)
Kanade: (And the only thing I can do for her right now is to keep composing.)
Kanade: (Still...)
Kanade: (Is that going to be enough to save her...?)
Kanade: (Listening to a song won't help resolve this situation. I can't save her from that person...)
Kanade: (Which means composing won't be enough...)
Kanade: (I have to do something more...)
???: <Kanade...>
Kanade: Huh? Luka...? Is something the matter?
Luka: <It's about time for you to bring a demo over for us to listen to, but you haven't been around to SEKAI at all.>
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: Sorry, I'm still not happy with what I have.
Luka: <Oh...?>
Luka: <Is that the only reason?>
Kanade: Huh...?
Luka: <Hehe. You don't have to answer now.>
Luka: <If you do feel stuck, then why don't you come over for a visit? A strange, new area just appeared.>
Kanade: A strange, new area...?
Luka: <Yes. You haven't been there yet, right? It may serve as good inspiration.>
Kanade: ...
Kanade: Okay...
Mafuyu: ...
Kanade: I'll be right back, Mafuyu. I'm going to go take a quick look.
Kanade: What's this new area like?
Luka: It doesn't quite fit into this SEKAI. I'm sure you're going to be surprised.
Kanade: I am...?
Kanade: Huh...? This song...
Luka: It's one of yours, no? You can hear it playing there from time to time.
Kanade: Wait, really? But why...?
Luka: Who knows? But you can tell while listening to it...
Luka: How Mafuyu needs your songs...
Kanade: She needs my...?
Luka: They must mean quite a lot to her...
Kanade: ...
Kanade: Does this mean I've actually been helping her?
Luka: Helping Mafuyu?
Kanade: Yes... I feel like this is evidence of that.
Kanade: But I still haven't been able to save her...
Kanade: Right now, I feel that I need to figure out a way to do more for her besides just composing songs.
Kanade: Um, Luka...?
Kanade: Luka...?
Kanade: Wait, where'd she go...?
???: *Sob*
Kanade: Huh...?
Kanade: Is someone crying...? But where...?
???: *Sob*
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (A little girl...?)
Kanade: (What's she doing here? No one besides us should be able to enter SEKAI...)
Kanade: (But something must've happened to make her cry... I should try to help her...)
Kanade: Um... What's wrong?
Girl: ...!
